=== Etymology ===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From Latinised Greek [[adamantinus]] "hard as steel", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[αδαμάντινος]]''' (''adamantinos'') "hard, unbreakable, hard as steel",   from '''[[αδάμας]]''' (''adamas'') "untamed, unconquerable, unbreakable, diamond", from 
'''[[α-]]''' "un-, not" + 
'''[[δαμάζω]]''' (''damazo'') "to overpower, to tame, to brake in, to subdue, to conquer".

===Adjective===
'''adamant'''
# resistant to reason; determined; inflexible; unshakeable; unyielding

===Noun===
'''adamant'''
# a rock or mineral imagined by some to be of [[impenetrable]] [[hardness]]; a name given to the [[diamond]] and other substances of extreme hardness
# an [[embodiment]] of [[impregnable]] hardness
# [[lodestone]]; [[magnet]]

